Lewis E 249b illustrates the devotional image of the Wheel of Sevens, including personification of the vices, with text explaining the diagram below. Two membranes appeared in the catalogue of Berlin dealer Paul Graupe in 1928, lot 7, pl. 5; one of the miniatures from these membranes is now at the Cleveland Museum of Art, 1954.388.
